This paper deals with the performance analysis of LDPC codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The study of combinatorial structures such as trapping sets and absorbing sets involves graph theory and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the asymptotic behavior of these structures, which is a topic in asymptotic analysis and probability theory (cs.CC, cs.SI). Finally, the analysis of LDPC codes involves the study of their degree distributions, which is a topic in network science and complex systems (cs.NI).
